│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs inside InstCombine when checking whether an instruction is   │
│ trivially dead. Specifically, Value::materialized_use_begin() asserts that    │
│ hasUseList() is true, but it's being called on a Value that does not maintain │
│ a use-list (notably PoisonValue). This happens during analysis of lifetime    │
│ intrinsics.                                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The log shows InstCombine visiting the alloca, then store to %arg, then store │
│ to poison. It replaces the alloca with ptr poison and erases the alloca.      │
│ Immediately after, the pass calls isInstructionTriviallyDead() on subsequent  │
│ instructions, which triggers wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead(). That function │
│ enters the lifetime intrinsic case and tries to iterate over uses of the      │
│ pointer argument via Arg->uses(). The backtrace matches Local.cpp:487, which  │
│ is precisely the lifetime case iterating uses. The crash happens at           │
│ Value::uses() because the Value (poison) lacks a materialized use-list.       │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead() assumes that the pointer operand to         │
│ llvm.lifetime.start/end has a materialized use list and iterates Arg->uses()  │
│ to check if all users are LifetimeIntrinsic. This assumption is false for     │
│ PoisonValue (and potentially other Values that don't maintain use lists).     │
│ InstCombine replaced the alloca with ptr poison, making the lifetime.end's    │
│ pointer argument be poison. Subsequently, wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead()   │
│ calls Arg->uses(), which asserts because hasUseList() is false on             │
│ PoisonValue.                                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Modify wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead() lifetime-intrinsic branch to guard   │
│ against Values without a use-list. If the pointer argument doesn't have a     │
│ use-list, then its users aren't tracked; in this context, the only known user │
│ is the current lifetime intrinsic. That satisfies the "only uses are lifetime │
│ intrinsics" condition, so we can conservatively treat the intrinsic as dead.  │
│ Concretely:                                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/Local.cpp                                   │
│ - Lines: 486-491                                                              │
│ - Change the block under II->isLifetimeStartOrEnd() to first check            │
│ Arg->hasUseList(). If false, return true; otherwise iterate Arg->uses() as    │
│ before.                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit:                                                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ Replace:                                                                      │
│   if (II->isLifetimeStartOrEnd()) {                                           │
│     auto *Arg = II->getArgOperand(1);                                         │
│     // If the only uses of the alloca are lifetime intrinsics, then the       │
│     // intrinsics are dead.                                                   │
│     return llvm::all_of(Arg->uses(), [](Use &Use) {                           │
│       return isa<LifetimeIntrinsic>(Use.getUser());                           │
│     });                                                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ With:                                                                         │
│   if (II->isLifetimeStartOrEnd()) {                                           │
│     auto *Arg = II->getArgOperand(1);                                         │
│     // If the only uses of the pointer are lifetime intrinsics, then the      │
│     // intrinsics are dead. Some Values (e.g. poison) do not maintain a       │
│     // materialized use-list; in that case, the only known user here is this  │
│     // intrinsic, so treat it as dead.                                        │
│     if (!Arg->hasUseList())                                                   │
│       return true;                                                            │
│     return llvm::all_of(Arg->uses(), [](Use &Use) {                           │
│       return isa<LifetimeIntrinsic>(Use.getUser());                           │
│     });                                                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By guarding the uses() iteration with hasUseList() and returning true when    │
│ the pointer operand lacks a use-list, we avoid the assertion on Values like   │
│ PoisonValue and correctly treat lifetime intrinsics as dead when their        │
│ pointer operand has no tracked non-lifetime users. This resolves the crash in │
│ InstCombine for the provided reproducer without affecting correctness of      │
│ dead-code elimination decisions.                                              │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
